{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["62-1JN-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"1JN"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["1 Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Yuhanna’s First Letter \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["1 Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["1Jn \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Yuhanna’s First Letter \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"1JN 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1JN 1:1"},"That which was from the beginning, that which we have heard, that which we have seen with our eyes, that which we saw, and\nour hands touched, concerning the Word of life \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1JN 1:2"},"(and the life was revealed, and we have seen, and testify, and declare to you the life, the eternal life, which was with\nthe Father, and was revealed to us); \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1JN 1:3"},"that which we have seen and heard we declare to you, that you also may have fellowship with us. Yes, and our fellowship is\nwith the Father, and with his Son, Al Masih Isa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1JN 1:4"},"And we write these things to you, that our joy may be fulfilled.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1JN 1:5"},"This is the message which we have heard from him and announce to you, that Allah is light, and in him is no darkness at\nall. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1JN 1:6"},"If we say that we have fellowship with him and walk in the darkness, we lie, and don’t tell the truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1JN 1:7"},"But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Al Masih Isa,\nhis Son, cleanses us from all sin. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1JN 1:8"},"If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1JN 1:9"},"If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us the sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1JN 1:10"},"If we say that we haven’t sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"1JN 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1JN 2:1"},"My little children, I write these things to you so that you may not sin. If anyone sins, we have a\nCounsellor",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek παρακλητον: Counsellor, Helper, Intercessor, Advocate, and\nComforter."]}],"caller":"+"}," with the Father, Al Masih Isa, the righteous. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1JN 2:2"},"And he is the atoning sacrifice",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“atoning sacrifice” is from the Greek “ιλασμος”, an appeasing,\npropitiating, or the means of appeasement or propitiation—the sacrifice that turns away Allah’s wrath because of our sin.\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the whole world.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1JN 2:3"},"This is how we know that we know him: if we keep his commandments.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1JN 2:4"},"One who says, “I know him,” and doesn’t keep his commandments, is a liar, and the truth isn’t in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1JN 2:5"},"But Allah’s love has most certainly been perfected in whoever keeps his word. This is how we know that we are in him:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1JN 2:6"},"he who says he remains in him ought himself also to walk just like he walked.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1JN 2:7"},"Brothers, I write no new commandment to you, but an old commandment which you had from the beginning. The old commandment\nis the word which you heard from the beginning. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1JN 2:8"},"Again, I write a new commandment to you, which is true in him and in you; because the darkness is passing away and the\ntrue light already shines. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1JN 2:9"},"He who says he is in the light and hates his brother is in the darkness even until now.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1JN 2:10"},"He who loves his brother remains in the light, and there is no occasion for stumbling in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1JN 2:11"},"But he who hates his brother is in the darkness, and walks in the darkness, and doesn’t know where he is going, because\nthe darkness has blinded his eyes. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1JN 2:12"},"I write to you, little children, because your sins are forgiven you for his name’s sake.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1JN 2:13"},"I write to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I write to you, young men, because you have overcome the evil one.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I write to you, little children, because you know the Father.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1JN 2:14"},"I have written to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I have written to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of Allah remains in you, and you have overcome the\nevil one. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1JN 2:15"},"Don’t love the world or the things that are in the world. If anyone loves the world, the Father’s love isn’t in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1JN 2:16"},"For all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh, the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, isn’t the Father’s, but\nis the world’s. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1JN 2:17"},"The world is passing away with its lusts, but he who does Allah’s will remains forever.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1JN 2:18"},"Little children, these are the end times, and as you heard that the Antichrist is coming, even now many antichrists have\narisen. By this we know that it is the final hour. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1JN 2:19"},"They went out from us, but they didn’t belong to us; for if they had belonged to us, they would have continued with us.\nBut they left, that they might be revealed that none of them belong to us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1JN 2:20"},"You have an anointing from the Holy One, and you all have knowledge.\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or, “know what is true”, or, “know all things”"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1JN 2:21"},"I have not written to you because you don’t know the truth, but because you know it, and because no lie is of the truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1JN 2:22"},"Who is the liar but he who denies that Isa is the Masih? This is the Antichrist, he who denies the Father and the Son.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1JN 2:23"},"Whoever denies the Son doesn’t have the Father. He who confesses the Son has the Father also.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1JN 2:24"},"Therefore, as for you, let that remain in you which you heard from the beginning. If that which you heard from the\nbeginning remains in you, you also will remain in the Son, and in the Father.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1JN 2:25"},"This is the promise which he promised us, the eternal life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1JN 2:26"},"These things I have written to you concerning those who would lead you astray.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1JN 2:27"},"As for you, the anointing which you received from him remains in you, and you don’t need for anyone to teach you. But as\nhis anointing teaches you concerning all things, and is true, and is no lie, and even as it taught you, you will remain in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1JN 2:28"},"Now, little children, remain in him, that when he appears, we may have boldness, and not be ashamed before him at his\ncoming. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1JN 2:29"},"If you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone who practices righteousness has been born of him.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"1JN 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1JN 3:1"},"See how great a love the Father has given to us, that we should be called children of Allah! For this cause the world\ndoesn’t know us, because it didn’t know him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1JN 3:2"},"Beloved, now we are children of Allah. It is not yet revealed what we will be; but we know that when he is revealed, we\nwill be like him; for we will see him just as he is. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1JN 3:3"},"Everyone who has this hope set on him purifies himself, even as he is pure.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1JN 3:4"},"Everyone who sins also commits lawlessness. Sin is lawlessness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1JN 3:5"},"You know that he was revealed to take away our sins, and no sin is in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1JN 3:6"},"Whoever remains in him doesn’t sin. Whoever sins hasn’t seen him and doesn’t know him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1JN 3:7"},"Little children, let no one lead you astray. He who does righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1JN 3:8"},"He who sins is of the Iblis, for the Iblis has been sinning from the beginning. To this end the Son of Allah was revealed:\nthat he might destroy the works of the Iblis. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1JN 3:9"},"Whoever is born of Allah doesn’t commit sin, because his seed remains in him, and he can’t sin, because he is born of\nAllah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1JN 3:10"},"In this the children of Allah are revealed, and the children of the Iblis. Whoever doesn’t do righteousness is not of\nAllah, neither is he who doesn’t love his brother. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1JN 3:11"},"For this is the message which you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1JN 3:12"},"unlike Qabil, who was of the evil one, and killed his brother. Why did he kill him? Because his deeds were evil, and his\nbrother’s righteous. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1JN 3:13"},"Don’t be surprised, my brothers, if the world hates you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1JN 3:14"},"We know that we have passed out of death into life, because we love the brothers. He who doesn’t love his brother remains\nin death. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1JN 3:15"},"Whoever hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life remaining in him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1JN 3:16"},"By this we know love, because he laid down his life for us. And we ought to lay down our lives for the brothers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1JN 3:17"},"But whoever has the world’s goods and sees his brother in need, then closes his heart of compassion against him, how does\nAllah’s love remain in him? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1JN 3:18"},"My little children, let’s not love in word only, or with the tongue only, but in deed and truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1JN 3:19"},"And by this we know that we are of the truth, and persuade our hearts before him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1JN 3:20"},"because if our heart condemns us, Allah is greater than our heart, and knows all things.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1JN 3:21"},"Beloved, if our hearts don’t condemn us, we have boldness towards Allah;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1JN 3:22"},"so whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do the things that are pleasing in his\nsight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1JN 3:23"},"This is his commandment, that we should believe in the name of his Son, Al Masih Isa, and love one another, even as he\ncommanded. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1JN 3:24"},"He who keeps his commandments remains in him, and he in him. By this we know that he remains in us, by the Spirit which\nhe gave us. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"1JN 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1JN 4:1"},"Beloved, don’t believe every spirit, but test the spirits, whether they are of Allah, because many false prophets have\ngone out into the world. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1JN 4:2"},"By this you know the Spirit of Allah: every spirit who confesses that Al Masih Isa has come in the flesh is of Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1JN 4:3"},"and every spirit who doesn’t confess that Al Masih Isa has come in the flesh is not of Allah, and this is the spirit of\nthe Antichrist, of whom you have heard that it comes. Now it is in the world already.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1JN 4:4"},"You are of Allah, little children, and have overcome them; because greater is he who is in you than he who is in the\nworld. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1JN 4:5"},"They are of the world. Therefore they speak of the world, and the world hears them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1JN 4:6"},"We are of Allah. He who knows Allah listens to us. He who is not of Allah doesn’t listen to us. By this we know the spirit\nof truth, and the spirit of error. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1JN 4:7"},"Beloved, let’s love one another, for love is of Allah; and everyone who loves has been born of Allah, and knows Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1JN 4:8"},"He who doesn’t love doesn’t know Allah, for Allah is love. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1JN 4:9"},"By this Allah’s love was revealed in us, that Allah has sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live\nthrough him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1JN 4:10"},"In this is love, not that we loved Allah, but that he loved us, and sent his Son as the atoning\nsacrifice",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“atoning sacrifice” is from the Greek “ιλασμος”, an appeasing, propitiating, or the means of\nappeasement or propitiation—the sacrifice that turns away Allah’s wrath because of our sin.\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," for our sins. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1JN 4:11"},"Beloved, if Allah loved us in this way, we also ought to love one another.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1JN 4:12"},"No one has seen Allah at any time. If we love one another, Allah remains in us, and his love has been perfected in us.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1JN 4:13"},"By this we know that we remain in him and he in us, because he has given us of his Spirit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1JN 4:14"},"We have seen and testify that the Father has sent the Son as the Saviour of the world.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1JN 4:15"},"Whoever confesses that Isa is the Son of Allah, Allah remains in him, and he in Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1JN 4:16"},"We know and have believed the love which Allah has for us. Allah is love, and he who remains in love remains in Allah,\nand Allah remains in him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1JN 4:17"},"In this love has been made perfect amongst us, that we may have boldness in the day of judgement, because as he is, even\nso we are in this world. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1JN 4:18"},"There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear has punishment. He who fears is not made perfect\nin love. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1JN 4:19"},"We love him, because he first loved us. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1JN 4:20"},"If a man says, “I love Allah,” and hates his brother, he is a liar; for he who doesn’t love his brother whom he has seen,\nhow can he love Allah whom he has not seen? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1JN 4:21"},"This commandment we have from him, that he who loves Allah should also love his brother.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"1JN 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1JN 5:1"},"Whoever believes that Isa is the Masih has been born of Allah. Whoever loves the Father also loves the child who is born\nof him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1JN 5:2"},"By this we know that we love the children of Allah, when we love Allah and keep his commandments.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1JN 5:3"},"For this is loving Allah, that we keep his commandments. His commandments are not grievous.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1JN 5:4"},"For whatever is born of Allah overcomes the world. This is the victory that has overcome the world: your faith.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1JN 5:5"},"Who is he who overcomes the world, but he who believes that Isa is the Son of Allah?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1JN 5:6"},"This is he who came by water and blood, Al Masih Isa; not with the water only, but with the water and the blood. It is the\nSpirit who testifies, because the Spirit is the truth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1JN 5:7"},"For there are three who testify:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Only a few recent manuscripts add “in heaven: the Father, the Word, and\nthe Holy Spirit; and these three are one. And there are three that testify on\nearth:”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1JN 5:8"},"the Spirit, the water, and the blood; and the three agree as one.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1JN 5:9"},"If we receive the witness of men, the witness of Allah is greater; for this is Allah’s testimony which he has testified\nconcerning his Son. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1JN 5:10"},"He who believes in the Son of Allah has the testimony in himself. He who doesn’t believe Allah has made him a liar,\nbecause he has not believed in the testimony that Allah has given concerning his Son.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1JN 5:11"},"The testimony is this, that Allah gave to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1JN 5:12"},"He who has the Son has the life. He who doesn’t have Allah’s Son doesn’t have the life.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1JN 5:13"},"These things I have written to you who believe in the name of the Son of Allah, that you may know that you have eternal\nlife, and that you may continue to believe in the name of the Son of Allah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1JN 5:14"},"This is the boldness which we have towards him, that if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1JN 5:15"},"And if we know that he listens to us, whatever we ask, we know that we have the petitions which we have asked of him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1JN 5:16"},"If anyone sees his brother sinning a sin not leading to death, he shall ask, and Allah will give him life for those who\nsin not leading to death. There is a sin leading to death. I don’t say that he should make a request concerning this.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1JN 5:17"},"All unrighteousness is sin, and there is a sin not leading to death.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1JN 5:18"},"We know that whoever is born of Allah doesn’t sin, but he who was born of Allah keeps himself, and the evil one doesn’t\ntouch him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1JN 5:19"},"We know that we are of Allah, and the whole world lies in the power of the evil one.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1JN 5:20"},"We know that the Son of Allah has come, and has given us an understanding, that we know him who is true, and we are in\nhim who is true, in his Son Al Masih Isa. This is the true Allah and eternal life.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1JN 5:21"},"Little children, keep yourselves from idols. "]}]}